      "text": "Discussion: The urbanist Jane Jacobs famously described “eyes on the street” as a form of stewardship of the public realm1. Residents, business employees, owners, members of civic institutions, and even visitors, all provide an informal network of governance, able to sense and react to problems as they occur. These can include responses to control criminal behavior, prevention or repair of damage to public structures, and mutual support during natural events like storms. Positive stewardship acts can include small repairs, beautification projects, artwork, and other improvements.",
